<br>
Basically you make a hotkey that says /twsit 1 2 3 4 or what have you and it does it. Another hotkey says /stoptwist.<br>
<br>
I will strip out all the advanced targeting, mapping, warping etc features so hopefully sony will be ok with using it just to twist. I prefer it over xylobot since XB has a slight lag, especially in large zones.<br>
<br>
The feature really should have been in the game from the start, I've put myself through hell a few times and swelled my wrists up to obscene sizes.<br>
<br>
[EDIT] This should really be like post 10, no idea what is going on here.<br>
<br>
The order of the posts is all messed up but I will PM the source code to anyone that wants it.<br>
<br>
What I won't do is send a pre-compiled version. Mainly because you have to re-compile every time there is a patch to update the memory locations (which can be found at the website of the program in question). So you will have to learn how to compile it yourself in any case.<br>
<br>
I don't have it finished yet, I'm basically just going through and stripping out part by part and seeing if it still works. Once I get all the crazy targeting and superuser stuff out of the program I will make an updated post.  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://b31.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pickkpockket999>Pickk Pockket999</A> at: 4/21/04 12:42 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://b31.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=duvane>Duvane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 104<br> <font color=#330000>(4/22/04 2:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19312.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: test</span><hr size=1> Like Liq said, they owe us a explanation.... i am sure there is a minute or 2 left over for some of their devs. <p>Duvane Dreamdance<br>
