<br>
-This is just a crippled version of MQ2. This means you have to live with the pain of updating the memory locations every time there is a patch, and also there is a debug window that you must set to 0 transparency.<br>
<br>
-I removed superwho, selectitem, target at a distance, putonto cursor, buyfrommerchant etc. Basically you can only run macros that solely involve keypresses, anything involving selecting spawns, targeting monsters, buying from merchants etc will simply not work.<br>
<br>
-You have to run MQ2auth.exe this authorizes it to run on your computer, then you compile the source code on your own machine. Feel free to improve upon it, just remember that if you make changes and want to distribute it you must include the source code since this is an open source project (and Lax is an amazing programmer, so give the dude some credit).<br>
<br>
-If you don't want to go through all this pain and suffering just to twist, buy Xylobot. I run EQ on a really crappy HD so XB is slow for me due to logging times. But if you have a zippy HD I hear it is just as fast, without the pain of compiling and updating memory locations.<br>
<br>
-After you compile, run the program and then load EQ. Once you get in EQ type /plugin mq2twist. You only have to do this the first time you load EQ. <br>
<br>
-Now whenever you want to twist songs just type /twist 2 3 4 5 for example. It doesn't do anything fancy, when you want to stop twisting type /stoptwist. Feel free to hotkey these commands.<br>
<br>
-This is an extremely grey area for sony. Whatever you do, under no circumstances leave the computer with this twisting macro running. You have been warned.<br>
<br>
One problem is I don't have space to host the files. So I guess we can do it by PM's, or if someone else has webspace to host it, that would be great. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://b31.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mearisthecowslayer>Mearis The Cowslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#330000>(4/22/04 8:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19312.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hmm</span><hr size=1> I would _HIGHLY_ reccomand you get an OK from a VI dev before you distribute that.<br>
