Take a sec to realize we are not complaining about the Bard class itself or its uniqueness, we are voicing our complaint to the physical pain it is causing us to play a class. Imagine if /attack was a button you had to hit every time it refreshed. Extreme but no one would have played. There are enough reasons to implement some common ground for those that are starting to get Doctor bills because of EQ that we are just asking for a break.<br>
<br>
This rant is both about the lack of concern EQ has for our pain, and the unfairness to the AA spent to gain marginal improvement over MORE button smashing.<br>
<br>
Everyone is entitled to their opinions, So please Allow Aeryon his with tasteful replies <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://b31.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yumako>Yumako</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#330000>(4/23/04 1:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19312.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.comcast.net/~toccard/lainani.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: missed notes log - 6.1% - WAKE UP SOE</span><hr size=1> I respect Tradezcat a lot. Playing a bard well is hard to do, and playing a good bard while having only one arm is even more amazing. He's a good bard who's done some awesome things by anyone's standards.<br>
<br>
Auto-twisting would be an awesome improvement for everyone, but an even better improvement is to dramatically cut down on the number of missed notes. It's obviously not difficult to program, as they let us not miss notes for that short period of time, and it would also really help out the entire bard community to not suffer so severely from burnout and carpel tunnel syndrome. Bards are definitely the only class that is so physically demanding to play and its a bit rediculous.<br>
<br>
For a long time many people liked that bards were so difficult to play. In fact, that's why I chose a bard myself is because I knew that playing a good bard would offer me the most challenge and reward out of any other class. However, with the amount of burnout we have been seeing as the game ages, and as WoW and CoH approach, we are losing players left and right. I don't want to see this game go down yet and I think one thing they could do is fix missed notes to add some longetivity back to a burned out class. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=772824">Yumako</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
