Allowing custom 3rd party programs opens up a large grey area/slippery slope.  People hear that macroing is allowed for twisting, so they go find a macro program ... potentially introducing programs that do -more- then just autotwist (like macroquest) to a larger portion of the userbase then would come across it without having macros sanctioned.<br>
<br>
It also opens up the customer service loop hole of people claiming the macro program that they got banned for using was &quot;just being used to twist songs, I swear!&quot;  Yes, I know... I know... what bannings for using a macro program... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :brickwall --><img src=http://members.cox.net/skoriksis/smilies/brickwall.gif ALT=":brickwall"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img src="http://lanys.evercrest.com/user-images/966/espiosig.jpg" align="left">
